The paper deals with the straight-line embedding of planar 3-trees, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The size of the point set required for the embedding is related to the complexity of the tree, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the class of 2-trees and serial parallel graphs, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of point sets for embedding is a common technique in computational geometry and visualization (cs.SI).
